{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01BZmtzr7jnn9Qxuh7kjvkAw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n\n1. **Elasticsearch** is running on port 9200 with TLS (Elasticsearch 8.x uses HTTPS by default)\n2. The `es-http` service exposes port 9200\n3. There's a `es-http-tls` secret in the `elasticsearch` namespace containing `ca.crt`, `tls.crt`, and `tls.key`\n4. The `es-http-tls` secret has:\n   - `ca.crt` - CA certificate chain\n   - `tls.crt` - Server TLS cert for `es-http` (looking at the cert CN, it includes `es-http` SANs)\n   - `tls.key` - Server private key\n5. The ingress-nginx controller is using NodePort (30195 for HTTP, 30993 for HTTPS)\n6. The ingress class is `nginx`\n\nMy approach will be to create a TLS secret for `es.example.com` in the elasticsearch namespace with a self-signed certificate, then set up an Ingress resource with TLS termination, SSL passthrough or HTTPS backend protocol configuration, and HTTP-to-HTTPS redirect. Since Elasticsearch's backend is already using TLS, I need to handle this carefully.\n\nI'm weighing two options: SSL passthrough where nginx forwards the encrypted connection directly to Elasticsearch, or TLS termination at the nginx level where I create a certificate for `es.example.com` and nginx handles the encryption before connecting to the backend via HTTPS. The second approach requires the backend-protocol annotation set to HTTPS. Given the requirements for HTTPS at `es.example.com` and blocking plain HTTP, I'll go with TLS termination at the ingress level. I'll use the `backend-protocol: \"HTTPS\"` annotation and redirect HTTP to HTTPS. The `es-http-tls` secret has a cert for `es-http`, not `es.example.com`, so I need to generate a self-signed cert for the ingress hostname using openssl—I can use the existing openssl-toolbox pod in the elasticsearch namespace to do this.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13317,"cache_read_input_tokens":30105,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13317},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0400c68f-cd33-4a8f-948d-9337832c6bae","uuid":"15c9ef1f-34f0-4bca-8683-8327de216915","request_id":"req_011Ccf2JnmWjT3vcMy25o8BX"}
